text: Baucau is a city in East Timor (Timor-Leste). It is east of the capital, Dili. About 16,000 people live there, making it the second largest town in East Timor by population. It is served by the Cakung Airport. The town was first started by Portugal as a trading center. ==References== Category:Cities in East Timor
title: Baucau
